This paper focuses on team design and performance in multiplayer online games, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and game theory (GT) concepts. The mixed-methods approach used in the study also involves social informatics (SI) and cybernetics (CY) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the implications of the findings for game design and theory, which could fall under the category of computer graphics (CC).
